//
SQL Server Express is a free, lightweight edition of Microsoft SQL Server, designed for small-scale applications and learning purposes. It provides core database functionalities but has limitations on storage, performance, and advanced features compared to paid editions.
SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) is a graphical user interface (GUI) tool used to manage SQL Server databases, including SQL Server Express. It allows users to write queries, manage databases, configure settings, and perform administrative tasks 
//
